      "writtenOn": "2026-07-14T08:45:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Reason for replacing contentTypeInHeader with acceptMediaType:\nContent-Type is a reserved HTTP header. Swagger UI does not send custom in: header parameters named Content-Type,\nwhich means contentTypeInHeader always arrives as null on the server side — making it non-functional.\nInstead, the Accept header is the standard HTTP mechanism for a \nclient to specify the desired response format (e.g., application/json or application/xml).",
